724166f-b.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - Barrow Street
724166f-b.text:
Washington Street, north from Barrow Street, showing mainly
the cleared west side of this thoroughfare. Upon same will be
enected the elevated roadbed of the New York Central Railroad
that extends from the St. JJohns Park Freight CCerminal and continues
uup the west side of Manhattan.
The low builcings to the left are on the north side of
Christopher Street, lyiig between WWashington and Weehawken
(extreme left) Streets.
View No. 3 emphasizes this feature mainly. The tall
smolestacks are those of the Bcadleston and Woerz Brewery
(.v.) which was razcd in the Summmwer of 1938.
Returning to View 1, one sees at the right margin a
portion of the U. S. Government building listed as the
Aprraisers Stores.
The Everards Storage Warehouse is to the north, same being
the 12 story structure bearing No. 667 Washington Street and located
at the N.E. corner of W. 10th Street.
September 24, 1930
Views: 1-2-3
